OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FAfghanistan: Ex-President  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FAshraf Ghani apologises for
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Ffleeing                    
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Former Afghan President Ashraf Ghani   
OL,6, has apologised to the people of        
OL,7, Afghanistan after fleeing to take      
OL,8, refuge in the United Arab Emirates.    
OL,10,F"Leaving Kabul was the most difficult  
OL,11,Fdecision of my life," he said, adding  
OL,12,Fthat he was sorry he "could not make it
OL,13,Fend differently".                      
OL,15,FMr Ghani abruptly left Afghanistan as  
OL,16,FTaliban militants advanced on the      
OL,17,Fcapital on 15 August.                  
OL,19,FHe said he had not intended to abandon 
OL,20,Fhis people but "it was the only way".  
